The volus homeworld, Irune, has a high-pressure atmosphere that supports an ammonia-based biochemistry. To survive on other planets, the volus must wear pressure suits and breathers or, when facing combat, specially sealed armor.
Volus are cagey support specialists that use the most technologically advanced power armor credits can buy.
$765358 Not to be underestimated, the diminutive volus adept more than makes up for its size with biotic abilities that are nothing short of godly.
$765358 Not to be underestimated, the diminutive volus engineer more than makes up for its size with cutting-edge gadgetry.
Repair your shields and those of nearby allies, providing a large initial boost to shields, and then restoring shields every second for a short time.
Reduce the delay before shields start regenerating by {Evolve_ShieldRegen%p}% for {Evolve_ShieldRegenDuration} seconds for you and affected allies.
Increase the duration that shields are restored by {Evolve_RestoreDurationBonus%p}%.

Increase shield restoration by {Evolve_ShieldBoost2%p}%, causing you and affected allies to take {Evolve_DamageReduction%p}% less damage for {Evolve_DamageReductionDuration} seconds. Total damage reduction from all sources cannot exceed {Evolve_MaxDamageReduction%p}%.
Repair your shields and those of nearby allies, providing a large initial boost to shields, and then restoring shields every second for {RestoreDuration} seconds.

Summon biotic orbs to float around you. Use the power again to launch an orb at your target. Each floating orb increases the recharge speed of your powers.
Highly effective against armor and barriers.

Summon {NumberOfOrbs} biotic orbs to float around you. Use the power again to launch an orb at your target. Each floating orb increases the recharge speed of your powers by {CooldownPerOrb%p}%.
Highly effective against armor and barriers.
Increase the recharge speed bonus of each orb by {Evolve_CooldownBonus%p}%.
Each orb impact causes the target to take {Evolve_DamageDebuff%p}% more damage from all sources for {Evolve_DamageDebuffDuration} seconds. This effect can stack up to {Evolve_MaxDebuffAmount} times.
Increase the number of orbs summoned by {Evolve_OrbIncrease}. This also boosts the maximum recharge speed bonus applied by the orbs.
Low-recoil submachine gun. High rate of fire, and effective against armor. Does not require thermal clips.

This short weapon is a hybrid of mechanical and organic parts, some more advanced than the Collector assault rifle. It vents heat automatically rather than requiring thermal clips and, when wielded by a Collector, extends a neural link to their skin at the wrist. Its ammunition is effective against armor and low recoil makes it a good weapon for sustained suppression.
Beam-based weapon capable of sustained fire. Does not require thermal clips.

This weapon's long-range particle beam is capable of sustained fire, allowing it to switch between anti-personnel or anti-materiel roles just by holding down the trigger. This rifle does not accept thermal clips, instead cooling down by venting heat into a liquid-containing sleeve that radiates it through the fin-like protuberances on its barrel.

A specially designed ops survival pack that temporarily increases survivability and all damage output.
A limited number of these packs can be carried.

Havoc soldiers belong to the turian's lethal 26th Armiger Legion, a respected and feared frontline assault squad. On the battlefield, the 26th use propulsion packs built into their armor to launch lightning-quick airstrikes on unsuspecting foes.

Ghost infiltrators belong to the turian's lethal 26th Armiger Legion, a respected and feared frontline assault squad. On the battlefield, a Ghost uses propulsion packs and advanced stealth technology to launch devastating airstrikes on unsuspecting foes.

Only one mine can be active at a time.

The geth trooper is an efficient and precise soldier capable of both offensive and support roles, impeding enemies with mines and supplementing its compatriots' shields.
The quarian marksman is a pugnacious tactician that, after assessing the situation, will just as soon blister the field with explosives as pick off enemies from a distance.
Often underestimated, volus mercenaries specialize in getting out alive to spend their hard-won pay. Recon mines, decoys, and orbs that boost biotics help maximize any team's survivability.
These volus cut their opponents off at the knees, whether by biotic charge or with anti-personnel weaponry. Unlike the reckless vanguards of other species, the volus bring mines to even the odds.
